      "writtenOn": "2017-07-11T00:03:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "well, not really. It\u0027s mixing two numbers in 0-256 range to produce some kind of average for them. |other.pendingBlend| is usually 256, meaning fully opaque picture. |blend| is how much less opaque you want it to become.\ne.g. 256 * 128 -\u003e 128 (you want to make the image half as transparent as it was)\nor 128 * 128 -\u003e 64 (same, now its alpha is 64/256)\nif either of values is 256 then it keeps the other value as is.\n\nThat\u0027s the simplest formula I could come up with",
      "parentUuid": "e8f2b9f2_362c9f7c",
